physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Fundus examination revealed an atrophic area around the optic discs, macular degenerations, and retinal thinning bilaterally. Central foveal thickness was measured at 175 µm for the right eye and 170 µm for the left eye.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: The patient reported deterioration of vision over the last few months, which is a progression from previous complaints of clarity problems for 5 years.
